{"lemma":"مَرْكَبٌ","slug":"مَرْكَبٌ","root":"ر.ك.ب","root_slug":"ر-ك-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ك-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16480"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"anything upon which one rides; ship, boat, vessel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"anything upon which one rides; saddle"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"compound, composed of multiple parts"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"compound"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Originally a noun of place meaning “place of riding”, from the verb رَكِبَ (rakiba, “to ride”). Cognate with Hebrew מֶרְכָּבָה (merkaḇa, “chariot”), Ge'ez መርከብ (märkäb), Classical Syriac ܡܰܪܟܰܒܬܳܐ.\n\nDerived from the passive participle of رَكَّبَ (rakkaba). Compare Hebrew מֻרְכָּב (murkáv, “complicated, complex”)."},"ipa":["/mar.kab/","/mu.rak.kab/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16480","headword_ar":"مَرْكَبٌ","root":"rkb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba","text_ar":"رَكِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, K, TA.) ―         -b2-  And also a noun of place [properly signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of riding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) [Hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything upon which one rides;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in, which one is borne"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carried:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAkib","text_ar":"مَرَاكِب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [more commonly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sea:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a beast"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on which one rides"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (A, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vessel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a ship"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, Msb, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a saddle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any kind of vehicle borne by a camel or other beast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the lexicons passim:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAkibu","text_ar":"مَرَاكِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the pl. (Mgh, Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEoma Almarokabu Ald~aAb~apu","text_ar":"نِعْمَ المَرْكَبُ الدَّابَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Excellent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most excellent, is the thing upon which one rides, the beast"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='ato maraAkibu Alyamani","text_ar":"جَا=ءَتْ مَرَاكِبُ اليَمَنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The vessels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ships"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boats, of El-Yemen came."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b3-  [And hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almarokabu","text_ar":"المَرْكَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The principal star"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Pegasus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because in the place of the saddle.]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","A","Mgh","Msb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}